at. 3377","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to chapter 87 (§ 6801 et seq.) of this title. For complete classification of title VIII to the Code, see Short Title note set out under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s6801"},"text":"section 6801 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id77fbfafe-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/328"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–328","children":[],"tail":" substituted “shall charge reasonable fees, in consultation with the Advisory Board and consistent with the Federal Lands Recreation Enhancement Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t16/s6801"},"text":"16 U.S.C. 6801","children":[],"tail":" et seq.),” for “may charge reasonable fees”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
